♬ That's exactly my song of love  ♬

124
00:12:37,910 --> 00:12:42,900
♬ Although the day is tiring ♬

125
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:47,860
♬ Your bright smile which I think of constantly ♬

126
00:12:47,860 --> 00:12:49,190
This really has no taste.

127
00:12:49,190 --> 00:12:57,550
♬ which makes me laugh for a moment ♬

128
00:12:57,550 --> 00:13:00,360
♬ Just with that alone. ♬
♬ Although for some still unexeplainable ♬

129
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:06,030
♬ Although for some still unexplainable ♬

130
00:13:06,030 --> 00:13:11,620
♬ Reason love emerges

131
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:17,700
♬ When like a habit the thought of you rises to the surface  ♬
♬ That's precisely my song of love ♬

132
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:24,860
♬ That's precisely my song of love ♬

133
00:13:26,930 --> 00:13:31,460
♬ My song of love ♬

134
00:13:46,370 --> 00:13:49,860
Will Sunbae Won be okay alone?

135
00:13:49,860 --> 00:13:54,220
I know. He's not the type of person who goes to the hospital when he's sick.

136
00:13:54,220 --> 00:13:57,150
He doesn't go to the hospital? Why?

137
00:13:57,150 --> 00:14:01,980
He doesn't have many memories of his mom being next to him when he's sick.

138
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:06,160
Handling it and enduring it by himself has become a habit.

139
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:09,440
Unfortunately, I have a long distance flight.

140
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:11,660
He has to eat well when he's sick though.

141
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:15,650
Ha Na will probably take good care of him.

142
00:14:15,650 --> 00:14:18,620
I better go home early and act like a noona.

143
00:14:18,620 --> 00:14:20,260
Okay.

144
00:14:25,650 --> 00:14:28,060
Aigoo.

145
00:14:28,060 --> 00:14:30,630
Is this starting again now?

146
00:14:30,630 --> 00:14:33,340
No way. She has her pride, too.

147
00:14:33,340 --> 00:14:37,870
No, that's not true. We heard her.

148
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:39,790
Stimulating maternal love.

149
00:14:39,790 --> 00:14:41,430
It's definitely possible.

150
00:14:41,430 --> 00:14:45,450
What does she like so much about him, huh? Truthfully, he's uglier than me.

151
00:14:45,450 --> 00:14:47,920
- Wow.
- This guy's a patient.

152
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,760
Nurse Jang, prepare for surgery.

153
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:53,380
Yes, I understand. Go to the hospital safely.

154
00:14:53,380 --> 00:14:55,860
Why are you all like this?

155
00:14:55,860 --> 00:14:59,520
Truthfully, I'm a pretty good person...

156
00:14:59,520 --> 00:15:02,630
Aish.

157
00:15:14,470 --> 00:15:21,530
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

158
00:15:33,180 --> 00:15:35,100
What is this?

159
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:42,820
The porridge I made yesterday... Did you eat it all?

160
00:15:42,820 --> 00:15:44,310
I threw it all away.

161
00:15:44,310 --> 00:15:48,120
What? That...

162
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,910
Then you should have told me to eat all of it.

163
00:15:49,910 --> 00:15:52,670
Aigoo, really.

164
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:57,990
But then, what was the treasure at the hideout yesterday?

165
00:15:57,990 --> 00:15:58,970
Not that important.

166
00:15:58,970 --> 00:16:00,440
What did you have?

167
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:03,600
One box of ice cream. I ate it all.

168
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:07,260
Isn't that why you got a stomach ache? You had a really high fever.

169
00:16:07,260 --> 00:16:10,870
Hey! Do you have enteritis?

170
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:14,510
Anyway, since I'm not all better yet, hurry up and go to work first.

171
00:16:14,510 --> 00:16:16,650
- Ah, but—
- Go!

172
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:18,060
Ugh, really.

173
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:21,880
Hey! If you're sick then go to the hospital!

174
00:16:28,460 --> 00:16:29,790
Director!

175
00:16:29,790 --> 00:16:33,600
Yes, ChaAndy Project will be on hold for now.

176
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:36,560
What? I'll take responsibility—

177
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:39,840
It's decided that this project can't be entrusted to you with only you  taking responsibility.

178
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:43,480
Everyone participating in the event today has already been cast,

179
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:46,200
- and regarding the company—
- Overall reexamination.

180
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:48,260
This is the company's point of view.

181
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:53,410
Pianist Cha Seo Hoo.

182
00:16:53,410 --> 00:16:55,780
Cha Seo Hoo, together with Tandy Shoes.

183
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:59,550
Thank you all for coming today, but regarding the content of the collaboration shoes,

184
00:16:59,550 --> 00:17:01,470
I apologize for not being able to relay it to you.

185
00:17:01,470 --> 00:17:03,860
With a report focusing on a charity soccer game...

186
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:05,860
Who decided that?

187
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:11,090
Wasn't I supposed to start with an interview today?

188
00:17:11,090 --> 00:17:15,980
Today's event... I thought the meeting of Tandy and Cha Seo Hoo was important.

189
00:17:15,980 --> 00:17:20,020
You know I'm not the type of person who does exclusive interviews.

190
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:21,000
You don't trust me?

191
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:26,920
I believe in ChaAndy Project. I will surely make it  a success.

192
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:30,170
Is there a special story in relation to the shoes?

193
00:17:30,170 --> 00:17:35,260
In the past, there was a person who thought what kind of shoes I wore was important.

194
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:40,940
She always cared for my shoes, saying my feet have to be comfortable in order for my performance to be comfortable.

195
00:17:40,940 --> 00:17:43,750
This seems like a dating experience.

196
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:44,390
Does it?

197
00:17:44,390 --> 00:17:47,700
Then perhaps, can I ask who that person was?

198
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:53,230
Since today is ChaAndy's charity event, I think I'll introduce the event first.

199
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:19,640
Fighting!

200
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,470
Fighting!

201
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:34,450
I made a goal. Are you not going to compliment me?

202
00:18:37,330 --> 00:18:40,000
Then compliment me once when the game finishes.

203
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:48,060
Good job!

204
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:04,830
Alright!

205
00:19:04,830 --> 00:19:08,700
How could you act like that even on Jeju Island?

206
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:12,960
Aigoo, really. Unbelievable, really.

207
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:17,170
Stop it. Why do you hold grudges?

208
00:19:17,170 --> 00:19:21,470
You went fishing during the whole three-day trip.

209
00:19:21,470 --> 00:19:24,480
I got seasick the whole time.

210
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:29,110
Would I have known that time would pass by so quickly? You should have said something then!

211
00:19:29,110 --> 00:19:31,910
I didn't say something? I said it so many times!

212
00:19:31,910 --> 00:19:36,020
Hyung Won is sick so he won't be able to go to work again today.

213
00:19:36,020 --> 00:19:38,500
What? Today too?

214
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:03,350
You came all the way here to find me?

215
00:20:03,350 --> 00:20:06,460
Since I couldn't find the person I have to care for.

216
00:20:09,610 --> 00:20:13,950
Ahhh, I'm hungry since I played a game.

217
00:20:13,950 --> 00:20:17,550
Let's eat here.

218
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:20,680
I don't want to eat bumping into people.

219
00:20:30,850 --> 00:20:34,340
I think it's the first time I've watched you play soccer.

220
00:20:36,330 --> 00:20:39,410
"First time." I like that.

221
00:20:40,110 --> 00:20:45,220
I mean eating together, playing piano, and fooling around...

222
00:20:45,220 --> 00:20:47,370
since that was all we did.

223
00:20:48,990 --> 00:20:53,020
What else could be a first? I should try finding out.

224
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:54,800
Right?

225
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:56,850
You don't have to do that.

226
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:03,150
There's a recital tomorrow. Let's go together.

227
00:21:04,970 --> 00:21:10,590
Even if I listen to it now, I think the recordings that I made when I was with you are the best ones.

228
00:21:10,590 --> 00:21:14,070
You were the one who rescued me again this time.

229
00:21:14,070 --> 00:21:18,860
You always seem to make me able to become the best.

230
00:21:22,730 --> 00:21:24,670
You're touched, huh?

231
00:21:26,010 --> 00:21:27,830
I'm not too sure about that.

232
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:33,250
What's more touching is...

233
00:21:34,630 --> 00:21:37,270
that what I'm saying is true.

234
00:21:46,420 --> 00:21:48,930
What do you do when you wake up in the morning?

235
00:21:50,170 --> 00:21:54,330
Exercise. I occasionally go jogging too.

236
00:21:56,730 --> 00:21:58,900
Exercise?

237
00:22:01,190 --> 00:22:04,180
Ta-da!

238
00:22:05,790 --> 00:22:08,210
Here!

239
00:22:09,940 --> 00:22:13,080
Look at his face all drawn.

240
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:16,050
Won. Eat a lot!

241
00:22:16,050 --> 00:22:20,710
I really don't have anyone but you. I really longed for your food.

242
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:22,710
Ah, I'm hungry!

243
00:22:22,710 --> 00:22:27,230
- Ah, you should give some to Father first.
- Don't bother!

244
00:22:27,230 --> 00:22:33,010
Yeah, Won. Eat a lot. You went through a lot of trouble eating Ha Na's food while you were sick.

245
00:22:33,010 --> 00:22:37,530
She's alright at everything else, but how can she be so bad at cooking?

246
00:22:37,530 --> 00:22:41,240
Why couldn't she be like her mom? There's no hope of her getting married.

247
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:45,330
You're right. It really wasn't something a human could eat.

248
00:22:45,330 --> 00:22:47,770
If she hears that, she's going to be extremely sad.

249
00:22:47,770 --> 00:22:50,090
Don't tattletale, Oh Dae Bok.

250
00:22:50,090 --> 00:22:53,570
But, did you have a nice trip to Jejudo?

251
00:22:53,570 --> 00:22:57,060
Aigoo, don't even talk about it.

252
00:22:57,060 --> 00:23:00,880
